# Webhook endpoint (configure in Stripe Dashboard):
#   https://<region>-<project>.cloudfunctions.net/stripeWebhook
# Events: checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.updated,
#         customer.subscription.deleted, invoice.payment_succeeded,
#         invoice.payment_failed
#
# =============================================================================
# StackHawk DAST (optional — local dynamic scans against stackhawk.yml)
# =============================================================================
#
# 1) Sign in / plan: https://app.stackhawk.com/  (Developer tier includes 1 app.)
# 2) Create an Application; copy its UUID into stackhawk.yml → app.applicationId
# 3) Account → API keys → create key (starts with hawk.)
# 4) In your shell (never commit the key):
#      export API_KEY=hawk.xxxxxxxx
#    Or add API_KEY to the StackHawk MCP server env in Cursor Settings → MCP
#    so `setup_stackhawk_for_project` / `run_stackhawk_scan` can authenticate.
#
# Scan with Docker (app must be running: npm run dev → http://localhost:8080):
#   npm run stackhawk:scan
#
# CLI alternative (install HawkScan locally): hawk scan
# Docs: https://docs.stackhawk.com/hawkscan/
